   <indicator ascending="0" measure="1">
    <title>
     <narrative xml:lang="EN">Output Indicator</narrative>
    </title>
    <description>
     <narrative xml:lang="EN">1.  # of outreach gender aware communication strategies developed and implemented to sensitized vulnerable communities on COVID 19 response;
2. # of visually impaired persons supported with COVID 19 sensitization messages using braille
3. # of vulnerable HHs supported with food and protective kits, based on the needs of women and men (disaggregated by female and male headed HHs.)</narrative>
    </description>
    <baseline year="2020">
     <comment>
      <narrative xml:lang="EN">1. No gender aware outreach communication strategy is in place
2. No visually impaired persons has been supported with COVID 19 response strategy using braille;
3.  No vulnerable HH is supported with food and COVID 19 protective kits</narrative>
     </comment>
    </baseline>
    <period>
     <period-start iso-date="2020-01-01"></period-start>
     <period-end iso-date="2020-12-31"></period-end>
     <target>
      <comment>
       <narrative xml:lang="EN">1. At least 3 (Radio, poster, manual etc.) gender responsive COVID-19 outreach strategies developed and implemented;
2. At least 1000 visually impaired persons supported with COVID-19 messages on braille;(disagregated by sex);
3. At least 3,750 (2250 Male headed HHs: 1500 Female headed HHs) households in 8 districts reached with food &amp; non food items &amp; hygeine kits.</narrative>
      </comment>
     </target>
     <actual>
      <comment>
       <narrative xml:lang="EN">1. Four outreach Covid 19 communication strategies were developed and implemented. They included; the production and distribution of 500 copies of COVID-19 Braille factsheet, 300 infographics in communities of persons with disabilities during awareness raising sessions on Covid 19, Social mobilization and the Distribution of 400 FM Radio sets to 400 school going pupils (children with disabilities and children of PwDs) with priority given to those in examination classes. 

2. More than 500 visually impaired persons were supported with 500 COVID-19 sensitization fact sheets on braille;

3.&#x2022;	With UNDP support, One Family People distributed 25 pcs of 200L Mila tanks &amp; 50 pcs of 30L Mila Tanks), 75 tissue box, 75 toilet rolls and 75 gel soap to 75 OPDs camps /offices including special needs schools to enable them to constantly practice the hygiene measures (washing hand). 
&#x2022;	400 bags (25kg) of rice, oil, onions and maggi were distributed to 400 children with disabilities and their families in 8 districts</narrative>
      </comment>
     </actual>
    </period>
